<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 18 at 7:20AM EDT until August 18 at 7:45AM EDT by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 745 AM EDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN WINDHAM...CENTRAL TOLLAND AND SOUTHEASTERN HARTFORD
COUNTIES...
At 719 AM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Bolton, or near
Vernon, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Manchester, East Hartford, Glastonbury, Vernon, Mansfield, Windham,
Willimantic, Tolland, Coventry, Hebron, Marlborough, Willington,
Columbia, Bolton, Ashford, Andover, Chaplin, and Scotland.
TORNADO...POSSIBLE
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
